lions-of-israeli-pensions-the-state-wont-protect-them/00000190-bb65-db47-abb0-bb7556920001</link><description>资本市场管理局承认，近一年来，在其监管下的养老金中，有数亿谢克尔被盗，但没有一个受害者被告知。但接受指责是另一回事</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 15:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-07-16/ty-article-magazine/.premium/a-huge-fraud-erased-hundreds-of-millions-of-israeli-pensions-the-state-wont-protect-them/00000190-bb65-db47-abb0-bb7556920001</guid></item><item><title>以色列公设辩护人：战时紧急立法严重侵犯囚犯权利</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/.premium/public-defender-emergency-legislation-during-the-war-infringes-on-rights-of-prisoners/00000190-bb73-de8b-adfc-bb73ea3c0000</link><description>根据公设辩护人办公室 2023 年活动报告，自以色列与加沙哈马斯战争爆发以来，提起的恐怖主义煽动起诉数量比过去四年还要多，同时对警察暴行的投诉也激增</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 15:06:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/.premium/public-defender-emergency-legislation-during-the-war-infringes-on-rights-of-prisoners/00000190-bb73-de8b-adfc-bb73ea3c0000</guid></item><item><title>数万名阿拉伯人居住在耶路撒冷，没有自来水：“它将成为第二个加沙”</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/palestinians/2024-07-16/ty-article-magazine/.premium/the-arabs-living-in-jerusalem-without-running-water-it-will-become-a-second-gaza/00000190-bb83-db81-a3f7-fb9fe9680000</link><description>耶路撒冷最大的城区缺乏自来水，似乎没有人关心：Kafr Aqab 的居民每周只能获得几个小时的水，无法洗衣服或洗地板，被迫放弃淋浴</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 14:09:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/palestinians/2024-07-16/ty-article-magazine/.premium/the-arabs-living-in-jerusalem-without-running-water-it-will-become-a-second-gaza/00000190-bb83-db81-a3f7-fb9fe9680000</guid></item><item><title>位智前首席执行官：“如果我们采取正确的步骤，新加坡将像我们旁边的加沙一样”</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/tech-news/2024-07-16/ty-article-magazine/.premium/if-we-take-the-right-steps-singapore-will-look-like-gaza-next-to-us/00000190-b1bc-df47-a7bf-b1be45b20000</link><description>10 月 7 日后的一天，以色列科技界最成功的人物之一诺姆·巴丁 (Noam Bardin) 在美国生活了 13 年之后回到了以色列。“这场巨大的危机为这个国家提供了一个‘重启’的机会，尽管代价高昂。” ，”他告诉《国土报》</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 13:47:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/tech-news/2024-07-16/ty-article-magazine/.premium/if-we-take-the-right-steps-singapore-will-look-like-gaza-next-to-us/00000190-b1bc-df47-a7bf-b1be45b20000</guid></item><item><title>以色列国防军告诉高等法院：许多坦克在战争中受损，弹药短缺</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/.premium/idf-tells-high-court-many-tanks-damaged-in-the-war-there-is-ashortage-in-ammunition/00000190-bb29-de8b-adfc-bb298b860000</link><description>针对女兵要求被允许在战斗岗位服役的请愿书，以色列军队回复称，由于战争，将推迟将女性编入装甲部队，该计划将于 2025 年 11 月启动</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 12:15:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/.premium/idf-tells-high-court-many-tanks-damaged-in-the-war-there-is-ashortage-in-ammunition/00000190-bb29-de8b-adfc-bb298b860000</guid></item><item><title>拜登：如果没有以色列，世界上每个犹太人都将面临危险</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/biden-without-israel-every-jew-in-the-world-would-be-at-risk/00000190-bac9-d458-a3d7-bbefa3f00000</link><description>拜登加强了对以色列的立场，称自己是犹太复国主义者。 “你不必是犹太人才能成为犹太复国主义者，”他在周一的采访中说。</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 10:22:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2024-07-16/ty-article/biden-without-israel-every-jew-in-the-world-would-be-at-risk/00000190-bac9-d458-a3d7-bbefa3f00000</guid></item><item><title>有一段时间，加沙人希望战争能够结束。现在他们感觉自己被抛弃了</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/news/middle-east/2024-07-16/ty-article/.premium/for-a-moment-gazans-had-hope-the-war-would-end-now-they-feel-theyve-been-abandoned/00000190-bab2-d211-a5da-fffb31440000</link><description>加沙人民说，世界只关心穆罕默德·德伊夫发生了什么，“没有人再谈论数十名死者了”。一位人权活动人士表示，过去曾有国际压力，但“现在，每个人都在等待内塔尼亚胡”</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2024 10:02:58 GMT</pubDate><guid i